Setting Description: Outcome (this will be used to organize results into folders)
Correct for cell phones (0 = no, 1 = yes)
External correction (0 = no; 1 = correct before; 2 = correct after)
Imputations (only relevant if there is an external correction model, applied before the small area model, and we need to propogate uncertainty)
Internal correction (0 = no; 1 = yes)
Years for internal correction (these are the years that set the level we want to predict at)
First year on which to fit the model
Last year on which to fit the model
Years of data to skip
Age groups
Model version
Year on which to center the data (ihme models only)
Window length for moving window approach (ihme models only)
Model should include a time RE (ihme models only)
Fit an initial state-level model to get empirical priors for the final model (0 = no; 1 = yes) (rw models only)
Model families to test (1-4)
Models with race (1) and without race (0)
Models with marital status (1) and without marital status (0)
Models with education (1) and without education (0)
Individual-level covariates to interact with age (assuming they are included as main effects)
Area-level covariates
First year of the validation period
Last year of the validation period
Validation type (pooled or unpooled)
Sample size cuttoff for counties in validation set
Sample down sizes (9999==in sample, all other numbers interpreted as actual sample sizes)
Iterations
Intervals over which to calculate changes with CI
